More than half the world's coral reefs endangered: IUCN
Marine life could take centuries to recover from killer waves byMadeleine Coorey
Beaches around South Asia devastated by tsunamis could be restored totheir former glory within a few years, but the marine life throughwhich the huge waves passed could take centuries to recover, expertssaid.
